Analysis of Target Structure  
•  Block Count & Layers  
  – There are 7 total blocks arranged in three “rows” (front to back).  
  – Front Row (Layer 1): Two red arch‐shaped blocks side by side.  
  – Middle Row (Layer 2): Two upright green rectangular blocks directly behind the arches.  
  – Rear Row (Layer 3): Three tall yellow rectangular pillars standing vertically behind the green blocks.  

•  Spatial Relationships  
  – Both red arches are placed flush against each other in a straight line.  
  – Each green block sits just behind (i.e.\, in the same left‐right position as) one of the arches.  
  – The three tall yellow pillars stand behind the green blocks\, spaced so that one is behind the left green\, one is centered\, and one is behind the right green.  

Selecting Required Blocks from the Dictionary  
1. Red Arch Blocks (2 needed)  
   – Use index 1 from the dictionary for each arch (it has the arch opening on the front face in the correct orientation).  
2. Green Upright Rectangles (2 needed)  
   – Use index 10 for each green block (tall orientation\, no rotation needed).  
3. Tall Yellow Pillars (3 needed)  
   – Use index 14 for all three yellow pillars (vertical orientation\, matching the target).  

Assembly Order  
{  
  Step1: Move block with index 1,  
  Step2: Move block with index 1,  
  Step3: Move block with index 10,  
  Step4: Move block with index 10,  
  Step5: Move block with index 14,  
  Step6: Move block with index 14,  
  Step7: Move block with index 14  
}
